description:
Under certain circumstances, code assist consumes too much code. The program needs a parameter added to the baz call in bar to make it correct. The code is as follows:

public class X {
    void bar(X x) {
        baz(x.foo());
    }

    int foo() {
        return 5;
    }

    void baz(int i, int j) {
    }
}

Steps to reproduce:
1. In the code, call the bar method on an instance of X: bar(x);
2. Observe that the code assist suggests code completion after x.foo().
3. Accept the code completion suggestion.
4. Observe that too much code is replaced.

Expected behavior:
When accepting the code completion suggestion, only the code after x.foo() should be replaced, not the entire line.

Additional information:
- The text to replace is computed by the code assist infrastructure.
- An option was added to control the amount of source code to replace.
- The option should be conditioned by a keystroke; pressing enter should replace until the end, and pressing insert should replace until the cursor location.

Note: The bug report mentions removing the option, but it is not clear from the description when or why it was removed.

OB:
Under certain circumstances, code assist eats too much code. The program needs a parameter added to the baz call in bar to make it correct. The code is changed to:

baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me:

baz(x.foo()x.foo())

